comments.body:
> Do we need a flag for this? I'd prefer not to add this, esp. if we're defaulting true.

It's another discovery call without caching that breaks the `--local` flag on some commands that usually won't be needed. Users that need it will know that they need it, so I could see setting it `false` by default, but I'd rather not have it be unconditional and thereby permanently disable flags in other commands.

@smarterclayton I know you feel strongly about unnecessary round-trips.
